{
  "id": "esp32-s3-nano",
  "name": "Waveshare ESP32-S3-Nano",
  "baseChip": "esp32s3",
  "pcb": "black",
  "notes": [
    "Arduino Nano form factor on the ESP32-S3R8 (16MB flash, 8MB PSRAM). Pin-compatible with the official Arduino Nano ESP32; select that board in the Arduino IDE.",
    "The B0 and B1 pads sit at the classic Nano's AREF and RESET positions but are GPIO46 and GPIO0, both boot strapping pins. B1 does not reset the board (use RST), and B0/B1 also drive the onboard RGB LED (GPIO46/0/45).",
    "Keep the onboard ceramic antenna clear of metal."
  ],
